Sentencas: Developing Fe -based high active and stable oxygen electrode materials is essential for commercializing solid oxide cells (SOC).
Titulo: Bismuth doped La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-δ perovskite as high active oxygen electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Herein, La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-delta (x = 0-0.3) oxides are synthesized and used as oxygen electrodes for oxygen reduction/evolution reaction (ORR/OER).
Titulo: Bismuth doped La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-δ perovskite as high active oxygen electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Bi-doping at La-site significantly improves the ORR/OER activity, producing high cell performance in fuel cell and electrolysis modes.
Titulo: Bismuth doped La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-δ perovskite as high active oxygen electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the polarization resistance of La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-delta is only 0.09 Omega cm(2), which is almost 3.5 times lower than undopedLa(0.5-x)Bi(x)Sr(0.5)Fe(0.9)Mo(0.1)O(3-delta) electrode.
Titulo: Bismuth doped La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-δ perovskite as high active oxygen electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the Ni-YSZ-supported full cell delivers a peak power density of 1237 mW cm(-2) in fuel cell mode and a current density of -2717 mA cm(-2) @ 1.5 V in electrolysis mode.
Titulo: Bismuth doped La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-δ perovskite as high active oxygen electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The electrolysis cell demonstrates an excellent durable operation for similar to 130 h under 500 mA cm(-2) and 750 degrees C. Therefore, the Bi doping strategy is effective for designing highly active oxygen electrodes of solid oxide cells.
Titulo: Bismuth doped La0.5-xBixSr0.5Fe0.9Mo0.1O3-δ perovskite as high active oxygen electrode for solid oxide cells
